olive oil
1 stalk celery
1 pear
1 carrot
1 packet ginger paste
2 packet beef strips
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bag parsley
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Thinly slice celery and pear. Grate the carrot.
• In a small bowl, combine Korean stir-fry sauce, ginger paste and a splash of water. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Return all beef to the pan, then add Korean sauce mixture and cook until slightly reduced and fragrant, 1 minute.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• While the beef is cooking, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, celery, pear, mayonnaise, the sesame oil and a drizzle of vinegar in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide sesame pear slaw between bowls. Top with Korean-glazed beef.
• Tear over parsley. Garnish with crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!